+const summary = [
+  "Analysis summary for ds001_prostate",
+  "",
+  `The dataset contained ${n} patients and a mean objective_response rate of ${fmt(mean(y))}. I used direct Parquet decoding, two-proportion response-rate comparisons, and linear-probability regression with heteroskedasticity-robust normal-approximation p-values. Effect estimates are absolute response-probability differences.`,
+  "",
+  "The dominant treatment signal was enzalutamide. In the adjusted main-effects model, treatment_enzalutamide was associated with a +0.202 absolute response-probability difference (p<1e-300), with unadjusted response 0.361 on enzalutamide versus 0.159 off enzalutamide. Other treatments did not show comparable main effects in the adjusted model.",
+  "",
+  "Disease state and biomarker main effects were strongly negative. mcrpc was associated with a -0.193 adjusted response-probability difference (p<1e-300). brca2_mutation and ar_v7_positive each carried about a -0.10 adjusted difference (both p<1e-300), and msi_high carried a -0.063 adjusted difference (p=2.35e-9). psma_high was not independently associated with higher response (effect -0.005, p=0.205).",
+  "",
+  "General health and tumor-burden markers also mattered. A one-SD higher ecog_ps was associated with -0.034 response probability (p<1e-300), one-SD higher weight_loss_pct_6mo with -0.022 (p<1e-300), one-SD higher albumin_g_dl with +0.010 (p=1.54e-8), and one-SD higher crp_mg_l with -0.009 (p=2.79e-8). PSA showed a smaller univariable gradient: moving from the 25th to 75th percentile changed response by -0.014 (p<1e-300). NLR, liver metastases, MET exon 14 skipping, and age did not show significant response gradients in the tested contrasts.",
+  "",
+  `The key heterogeneity finding was that enzalutamide benefit was concentrated outside mCRPC. The adjusted treatment_enzalutamide by mcrpc interaction was ${fmt(results.h14.effect)} (p=${fmtP(results.h14.p_value)}). In mcrpc=0 patients, response was ${fmt(results.h15.p1)} on enzalutamide versus ${fmt(results.h15.p0)} off enzalutamide (RD ${fmt(results.h15.effect)}, p=${fmtP(results.h15.p_value)}). In mcrpc=1 patients, response was ${fmt(results.h16.p1)} versus ${fmt(results.h16.p0)} (RD ${fmt(results.h16.effect)}, p=${fmtP(results.h16.p_value)}), not statistically significant. A joint model including both enzalutamide-by-mCRPC and enzalutamide-by-AR-V7 found residual AR-V7 attenuation of enzalutamide response of ${fmt(results.h17.effect)} (p=${fmtP(results.h17.p_value)}).`,
+  "",
+  `Several clinically plausible precision-treatment hypotheses were not supported. Abiraterone did not show AR-V7-specific attenuation (interaction ${fmt(results.h18.effect)}, p=${fmtP(results.h18.p_value)}). Olaparib did not show greater response in BRCA2-mutated patients; the interaction was negative (${fmt(results.h19.effect)}, p=${fmtP(results.h19.p_value)}), and within BRCA2-mutated patients response was ${fmt(subgroupBrcaOlaparib.p1)} on olaparib versus ${fmt(subgroupBrcaOlaparib.p0)} off (RD ${fmt(subgroupBrcaOlaparib.effect)}, p=${fmtP(subgroupBrcaOlaparib.p_value)}). Pembrolizumab did not show MSI-high enrichment (interaction ${fmt(results.h20.effect)}, p=${fmtP(results.h20.p_value)}; MSI-high subgroup RD ${fmt(subgroupMsiPembro.effect)}, p=${fmtP(subgroupMsiPembro.p_value)}). Lu-177-PSMA did not show PSMA-high enrichment (interaction ${fmt(results.h21.effect)}, p=${fmtP(results.h21.p_value)}; PSMA-high subgroup RD ${fmt(subgroupPsmaLu.effect)}, p=${fmtP(subgroupPsmaLu.p_value)}). Docetaxel did not show a visceral-metastasis-specific advantage (interaction ${fmt(results.h22.effect)}, p=${fmtP(results.h22.p_value)}), and autoimmune disease did not significantly attenuate pembrolizumab response (interaction ${fmt(results.h23.effect)}, p=${fmtP(results.h23.p_value)}).`,
+  "",
+  "Overall, this cohort's response structure was driven less by expected targeted-therapy biomarker enrichment and more by a broad disease-state/prognostic axis plus a highly subgroup-dependent enzalutamide association. The strongest supported pattern was high enzalutamide-associated response in non-mCRPC patients, with marked loss of that association in mCRPC and additional attenuation with AR-V7 positivity.",
+  "",
+].join("\n");
+
+fs.writeFileSync("transcript.json", JSON.stringify(transcript, null, 2));
+fs.writeFileSync("analysis_summary.txt", summary);
+
